<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n35235c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35235c">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35235c"> 235(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Heriot</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In connection with their lands at Baskin in the conty Dublin the Guild enjoyed the right of &ldquo;<mark>heriot</mark>.&rdquo; This was an incident of the feudal tenure of land under which the lord was entitled on a change in the tenancy to claim the best beast, be it horse or ox. <small> John J. Webb, <a name="JJWG" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JJWG"><cite title="source">The Guilds of Dublin</cite></a> (Jun 1929) 81</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
